        <story title="Tips" state="story done" points="10" mksid="1413490" relid="04">
            <slides>
                <slide type="story-context">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Each team has his own xsl!</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Remaining consistent decks over different teams requires either:</li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>one central xsl &amp; templates</li>
                                <li>sync changes between team xsl's</li>
                            </ul>
                        </ul>
                        <li>Use an assisted editor like Eclipse</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>realtime validation through xsd</li>
                            <li>code completion</li>
                            <li>syntax highlighting</li>
                        </ul>
                        <li>Run xsl tranformation for xsl editing</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li><a href="img/EclipseLaunchConfigurations.rar">easy launch configuration xsd transformations (import into eclipse)</a></li>
                            <li>Feedback xsl transform. in Console View</li>
                        </ul> 
                        <li>Refresh-in-browser review.xml when editing the deck</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Open de review.xml directly in browser</li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>firefox: go to <a target="_blank" href="about:config">about:config</a></li>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>disable (set 'false') security.fileuri.strict_origin_policy flag</li>
                                </ul>
                                <li>chrome: </li>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>start chrome with "chromium-browser --disable-web-security"</li>
                                </ul>
                            </ul>
                        </ul>
                    </ul>
                </slide>
            </slides>
        </story>
